name: Solaris Token
description: A currency for the Murderous Midsummer event.

name: Small lootchest
description: 3 random items, with a chance of a rare or better.

name: Medium lootchest
description: 5 random items, with a chance of a rare or better.

name: 5 Loot crates
description: Five medium lootcrates

name: Large lootchest
description: 7 random items, with a guarantee of at least one rare or better.

name: Epic lootchest
description: 9 random items, with a guarantee of at least two rare or better.

name: Welcoming Basket
description: Your friends have invited you into the world of Wolflord, an online social deduction game. As a token of friendship, you have been given a free copy of the game to keep, and this basket of goodies can be traded in for glorious treasures ingame.

name: Friendship Pack
description: This pack can be granted to a friend, and will turn into a free copy (to keep forever) of the online Wolflord game. Use the game client to utilize this item.

name: Vile Concoction
description: Triples the chances of becoming the Plague Lord. Will only be consumed when successful.

name: Professor Gladsbury
description: Promotional avatar from the other Lizardfactory game; Last Will.

name: Charity Portrait : Wolfbuddy
description: Charity portrait. Normally, 10% of the profits from this game goes to our wildlife charity friends. With this item, you can show your true filantropist side and in return, we will donate 100% of the revenue from this sale to the wildlife wolf preservation organizations.

name: Geckoface
description: A face reserved for Gecko the Developer.

name: Captain
description: Nothing goes past him when he is on duty. Not crime, not werewolves and definitely not bribes...

name: Fire mage
description: Spends so much time telling his fellow townsfolk that he's not a pyromaniac, that people are starting to get worried.

name: Dullface
description: The first face to ever appear in the game. My how we have grown...

name: Stabby McStabface
description: He'll cut ya!

name: Branson
description: Never fear, Branson is here!

name: Gork
description: Gork doesn't like when people are trying to get him lynched. Gork doesn't like that at all...

name: Songard
description: Despite his knee-arrow-incident, Songard is still a loyal member of the towns guard.

name: Grimlock
description: Stay awhile and listen... Or... Ignore what I'm saying and just lynch randomly... There we go...

name: Stunwin
description: Did somebody say... bonus votes?

name: Xarlaxx the Devourer
description: He will consume you all, one sloppy slimy bite at a time.

name: Crystal Elemental
description: A golemancer has to work with what he has...

name: Gnargnar
description: Bite bite bite bite BITE!

name: Gorlakk
description: Not every orc passes Village Sensitivity Training...

name: Wurgen
description: Wurgen made a promise that he could be in the game if he promised to stop stealing people's toes. But keep an extra eye on him, just to be safe.

name: Wur the Wererabbit
description: Hide your veggies, the wererabbit smells your delicious produce!

name: Zurimal
description: Doesn't buy into the rumors of these "alledgedly" bloodsucking vampires...

name: Barkbreathe
description: In the woods lives many spirits. Some kind, some cruel. Barkbreathe sees them all, but on who's side is he on?

name: Yelling Yark
description: THEY SAY IF I YELL TO THE CORNER I GET MORE DOWNLOADS ON THE APPSTORE!!!1!!

name: Zeevil The Bonemerchant
description: Zeevil has many wares... Well.. Many is a broad term. They're mostly just bones.

name: Gurnok, Overlord Of The Meek
description: His major plan is to inherit the entire earth.

name: Thrull
description: Might have a captivating backstory, but his appeal is highly compromised with his grueling underbite.

name: Awarewolf
description: You might all wake up in the morning, but the Awarewolf is fully woke at all times.

name: Zlarp
description: Zlarp leaps from the bushes to throw shade and insults. Zlarp has much to learn about how this game works...

name: Were-eel
description: When the moon strikes full, he seeks the nearest stream to spread havok to all salmon-kind.

name: Mad Sweeney
description: The secret ingredient to his cointrick is straight up robbery...

name: Mothrantula
description: Behold the light, my brother - It's glory will lead us all to everlasting bliss.

name: Skeleton King
description: Once he reigned supreme over the land of trumpets, but now his bony hands can barely play a tune.

name: Ravenlord
description: Was born with numerous raven-like traits, like digging tunnels and building ballistic towers.

name: Werepolarbear
description: Don't let the icecaps melt.

name: Skeleton Guard
description: If he catches you stealing, your boned.

name: Kyrikyh
description: Stalking his pray and fond of plums, it's wise to stay far far away from this wild creature.

name: Zipzlarp
description: His dentist bills are through the roof.

name: Midgrunn
description: He has lived since the dawn of time, and heard any bad excuse you could possibly dream up.

name: Implinni
description: If you ask him to bite your shiny metal behind, he will gladly oblidge.

name: Carvarr
description: Flesh is tasty, he carries knives, don't ask questions.

name: Warthauk
description: Abandoned by his master, the hungry demon Warthauk travelled the world, and was quickly recognized as both polite and friendly to everyone, despite his heritage.

name: Obsidian King
description: It rests, it stares, it rules over the land from his somber shell.

name: Toothfairy
description: Turns out, not as innocent as in the childrens tales...

name: Schredder
description: Has a strong passion for elegant engineering and a crippeling fear of turtles.

name: Glump
description: Will take all his earnings in unmarked flies, thank you.

name: Crabraxxulo
description: Even with his hard exoskeleton, Crabraxxulo is really a nice guy once you get beneath the hard exterior.

name: Glurb
description: Despite being made of sand and clay, Glorb is suprisingly bad at beach parties.

name: The Hollow Knight
description: True story, this game was originally ment to be named Hallownight, until the game Hollow Knight launched. Despite not being the same name, it called for a complete rebranding...

name: Wizyr
description: Hurricanes usually cause havoc and pain for thousands. This one can only cause mild annoyance at parties...

name: Rotface
description: Not holding back on honest details about herself on her social media profile...

name: Werewhale
description: Unless you are plankton, the Werewhale doesn't strike that much fear in your heart as most other were-creatures do...

name: Bugchump
description: There lives a chump in the bog, who likes to chomp on bugs...

name: Donnaturtle
description: Many bizarre creatures have been sighted in the waterways beneath the city of Jorke.

name: Spycrab
description: This magnificent creature is said to carry the ability to become both invisible, and completely distinguisable from your fellow townspeople..

name: Porkalak
description: For a creature not bigger than a fist, at least it has a bit that can take off more than it can chew.

name: Grillmiser
description: Master of the imps down below, and host of the annual Imp Barbeque. Now is it FOR the imps or is it USING the imps? We chose never to ask.

name: Snoutwing
description: In a game with hybrids like man-wolves and cat-burglars, this cross of a pig and a bat hoped he could fit right in.

name: Gloomguard
description: At the end of the darkness, just beyond the last thing you can see in the night, stands the Gloomguards. Ever vigitalt, ever watching, ever waiting...

name: Golek
description: Many sentient statues chose a somewhat somber look, to disguise themselves in towns and buildings. Golek however, does not. You go Golek, you do your thing and let nothing stop you!

name: Kokobow
description: The rare ridable birds of Karlmann was not to be messed with before, but their landspeed and ability to cross any landscape is a feat indeed.

name: Nighsight Oracle
description: The wisest of the underworld demons, the Nighsight Oracles can whisper words in your ears, unlocking millenia of wisdom. But none has lived to use this knowledge, before the hunger of the oracles set in...

name: Sulk
description: Don't get him sad. You wouldn't like him when he's sad...

name: Twisted Toad
description: Ignore the toad if it ask you to lick him, don't fall for his tales of princedom and wishes...

name: Skullrider
description: On his fiery steed he rides, and... well.. He's on fire. Besides that, not much to say really.

name: Yetmii
description: Lost to the frozen Winterwoods of the north, the mighty Yetmii is not a creature you wish bumping into in a snowstorm.

name: Obsidian Guard
description: Obsidian is the latest craze in evil armor making, forget that it's a very fragile rock. Black armor is the trendiest thing ever!

name: Minter
description: Master of coins and keeper of scales, the minter can tell a real coin from a fake at over 50 yards.

name: Grandfather's Cane
description: A rare heirloom from your estranged relative. Can be unlocked in the game Last Will.

name: Hucan the Tucan
description: Hucan the Tucan is one mighty fine bird.

name: The Watcher
description: A famous hero from across the land, defeated countless orcs singlehandedly, fond of long corpse-runs along the coast.

name: Desperate merchant
description: Please good sir, would you purchase some of his wares? He has so many mouths to feed, and so many adventurers do not give him the time of day...

name: Garlic Merchant
description: Spouter of exposition, giver of quests, dreamer of dreams... And also occasionally seller of garlic.

name: Achievement Hunter
description: Blazing through the land (and all the content) the Achievement Hunter has little time to stop and smell 10 Village Roses.

name: Optimistic Fisherman
description: It's always a nice day for fishing! Hu-hyurk!

name: Honeywood Maiden
description: The developers wants you to know that there are NO achievements for murdering maidens, so please stop trying!
